{"key":"processedPost-16053020","value":{"id":16053020,"first":15885220,"last":17046253,"when":1333743970,"utime":"04/06/12 11:26 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Veil said:</strong><br />Thanks and that is foil TAPE on the sides of the tubs to prevent bottom and side pinning.</blockquote><br />Foil on the sides of a tray <i>encourages</i> side pinning.&nbsp; As the substrate is consumed by the mycelium, it shrinks and pulls away from the edges, creating a microclimate conducive to pin formation.&nbsp; Adding foil causes light to be reflected into this void, increasing the likelihood of side and bottom pins. <br />Those chinese shelf units from Lowes are crap.&nbsp; In six months they'll be so rusty you'll never get them apart.&nbsp; I bought some for my mini-greenhouse a few years ago, and after a year I had to cut them in pieces with a hack saw just to get them to the dumpster.&nbsp; They won't affect your mushrooms, but don't cut yourself while tending to your project.<br />RR"}}